  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Key Accounts Executive (Modern Trade)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Account Management &amp; Business Development<br>\n</strong>Manage and grow sales performance across key modern trade accounts (FairPrice, Cheers, DFI, etc.).<br>\nBuild and maintain strong business relationships with category buyers, trade marketing teams, and retail partners.<br>\nNegotiate trading terms, listing opportunities, shelf space, and promotional support with buyers to maximize visibility and profitability.</li>\n  <li><strong>Sales Target Achievement<br>\n</strong>Develop and implement sales plans to achieve monthly, quarterly, and annual sales targets.<br>\nMonitor sales performance by channel and account, analyzing gaps and proposing corrective action plans.<br>\nTrack competitor activities and market trends to identify opportunities for growth.</li>\n  <li><strong>Promotions &amp; Trade Marketing<br>\n</strong>Plan, prepare, and submit promotional calendars and proposals in alignment with brand and customer objectives.<br>\nCoordinate with marketing and supply chain teams to ensure smooth execution of promotions, product launches, and in-store campaigns.<br>\nEvaluate post-promotion results and provide insights for continuous improvement.</li>\n  <li><strong>Merchandising &amp; In-store Execution<br>\n</strong>Lead, coach, and manage a team of merchandisers to ensure effective shelf display, planogram compliance, and on-ground execution.<br>\nConduct regular store visits to monitor merchandising standards, stock availability, and competitor activity.<br>\nEnsure visibility and share-of-shelf objectives are achieved in all assigned accounts.</li>\n  <li><strong>Reporting &amp; Administration<br>\n</strong>Prepare and analyze sales reports, promotion evaluations, and account performance reviews.<br>\nManage budget allocations for trade spend and ensure ROI on promotional activities.<br>\nEnsure timely submission of proposals, promotional mechanics, and administrative requirements from customers.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3><strong>Key Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Business, Marketing, or related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2–3 years of experience in Key Account Management or Sales within FMCG/Modern Trade.</li>\n  <li>Strong negotiation and communication skills with proven track record in handling key modern trade retailers.</li>\n  <li>Analytical mindset with ability to interpret sales data and market trends.</li>\n  <li>Proactive, results-driven, and able to work independently as well as in a team.</li>\n</ul>",
